  <h1 class="gd-h1">Iceland vs Norway for Heliskiing</h1>
  <p class="gd-lede">The short answer: both are Arctic sea-to-summit destinations, but Iceland is the more organised, rolling, single-base and accessible option, while Norway is wilder, steeper, more committing and touring-flavoured. Below we compare them honestly and give you a clear framework — see our <a href="/packages">packages</a> and our <a href="/iceland">Iceland</a> page.</p>
</div></section>
